    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Of a plane figure or a solid, a set of points containing all points in a line joining any two constituent points, for example, the rounded outward exterior curve of a circle or sphere. In a convex polygon, every internal angle is less than or equal to 180 degrees.</Note_Text>
